    <h1>UNO Stacking Rules — Can You Stack +2 and +4 Cards?</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">The complete answer to UNO's most argued-about rule — and how to play with stacking online for free.</p>

    <h2>Can You Stack Cards in UNO? The Official Answer</h2>
    <p>Officially: <strong>no</strong>. Mattel's official UNO rules do not allow stacking. If someone plays a Draw 2 on you, you draw 2 cards and lose your turn — you cannot play your own Draw 2 to pass the penalty along. Mattel has even confirmed this on social media, to the heartbreak of millions.</p>
    <p>But here's the thing: <strong>almost everyone plays with stacking anyway.</strong> It's the world's most popular UNO house rule, and it's a core rule in UNO No Mercy. That's why our game lets the host turn stacking on or off — you choose how brutal your table is.</p>

    <h2>How Stacking Works in Our Game</h2>
    <p>We don't just have one stacking switch — the host controls each type separately in a Custom room:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>➕ +2 Stacking</strong> — Someone plays a +2 on you? Play your own +2 instead of drawing. The next player must draw all 4 cards (or stack again for 6, 8, 10…).</li>
      <li><strong>✳️ +4 Stacking</strong> — Wild +4 cards stack on each other the same way. With our Wild +8 cards in the deck, piles grow terrifyingly fast.</li>
      <li><strong>🌀 Mixed Stacking</strong> — The spicy one: play a +2 on a +4, or a +4 on a +2. Every draw card answers every other draw card.</li>
      <li><strong>🛡️ Skip Dodge</strong> — Facing a big draw pile? Play a Skip of the matching color to save yourself — the next player draws instead of you.</li>
      <li><strong>🪃 Reverse Bounce</strong> — Even crueler: play a matching-color Reverse and the whole pile goes back to the player who sent it.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Can You Stack a +2 on a +4?</h2>
    <p>In official rules, no — you can't stack anything. As a house rule, tables disagree: some allow only same-card stacking (+2 on +2), others allow cross-stacking. In our game this is exactly the <strong>Mixed Stacking</strong> toggle — turn it on for full chaos, or leave it off so only matching cards stack.</p>

    <h2>What Happens When You Can't Stack?</h2>
    <p>The pile stops with you. You draw every accumulated card at once — we've seen players draw 20+ cards from a long stack chain — and your turn is skipped. In <a href="/uno-no-mercy">UNO No Mercy mode</a>, collecting 25 cards eliminates you from the game entirely.</p>

    <h2>Play UNO With Stacking Online — Free</h2>
    <p>Stacking is built into our free browser game. Turn it on two ways:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/uno-no-mercy">No Mercy mode</a></strong> — stacking of every kind is always on, plus elimination at 25 cards.</li>
      <li><strong>Custom mode</strong> — toggle each stacking rule individually and mix in other <a href="/house-rules">house rules</a>.</li>
    </ul>

